&lt;p&gt;Alternatively you can review and apply these changes as the patch at:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/tika/pull/26.patch&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/tika/pull/26.patch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To close this pull request, make a commit to your master/trunk branch&lt;br/&gt;
with (at least) the following in the commit message:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    This closes #26&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;commit 05340a8ef401a29206b7dff30b97d193347cd8c2&lt;br/&gt;
Author: Andrew Hwang &amp;lt;archerrbgh@gmail.com&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Date:   2015-02-02T07:08:19Z&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Added argLine value for maven-surefire-plugin&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Setting a higher maximum amount of memory prevents TestChmExtraction&lt;br/&gt;
    from generating an OutOfMemory error from running out of heap space&lt;br/&gt;
    when running parser tests and trying to install Tika 1.7 on OS X&lt;br/&gt;
    10.10.2.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14300954" author="tpalsulich" created="Mon, 2 Feb 2015 07:12:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Have you tried setting the MAVEN_OPTS environment variable, instead? It&apos;s good to avoid hard coding memory requirements. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14300966" author="hwanga" created="Mon, 2 Feb 2015 07:30:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Tyler,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I had already tried setting the MAVEN_OPTS environment variable, but it continued to fail. I did some searching around on Google, and found this from StackOverflow: &lt;a href=&quot;http://stackoverflow.com/questions/4066424/java-lang-outofmemoryerror-java-heap-space-in-maven&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://stackoverflow.com/questions/4066424/java-lang-outofmemoryerror-java-heap-space-in-maven&lt;/a&gt;. From what I could gather, the maven-surefire-plugin forks a new JVM and the amount of memory set in MAVEN_OPTS is not passed onto the new JVM.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
